at guideline. I'm pondering if we should add new tests, but it might be better to avoid that. If the provider SPI public method doesn't necessitate reflection, we should find an alternative. However, if previous attempts missed covering the KeyFactory provider route, this approach might finally address that gap!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating key implementation**\\n\\nI'm checking a potential issue with `DERInteger` in my key processing. I need to make sure that my assertion matches DHPrivateKey correctly. I wonder if there's a compilation issue due to `KeyFactorySpi` having the same name as a standard element—but it seems okay. I should verify that the `generatePrivate` method is public, which it is. Overall, I want to keep my implementation concise moving forward.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Refined the active-class test:\n\n- Updated `tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15on/1.48/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk15on/BCElGamalPrivateKeyTest.java`\n\nChange made:\n- Replaced the `BouncyCastleProvider` / JCA `KeyFactory.getInstance(...)` creation path with direct construction through Bouncy Castle’s public `KeyFactorySpi.generatePrivate(PrivateKeyInfo)` API.\n- This avoids provider algorithm loading and should more reliably create an actual `BCElGamalPrivateKey` instance before serialization.\n\nThe test still serializes and deserializes the key, targeting the remaining uncovered dynamic-access call sites:\n\n- `BCElGamalPrivateKey.writeObject(...)`\n- `BCElGamalPrivateKey.readObject(...)`\n\nI did not run tests locally, per instructions.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f0685683da137fd0169fbe32fa6e481928005fb8f717b1b14\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 711, "output": 770, "cacheRead": 30208, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31689, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "t