ary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating TCK Logic Changes**\\n\\nI'm considering whether I can modify the TCK logic. The rule is not to broaden patches with unrelated features, but I might need to accurately count coverage for no-line classes. The user mentioned focusing on the active class only and not changing the infrastructure. I wonder if adding a tiny wrapper subclass would be feasible. Since BCElGamalPrivateKey is public but has package-private/protected constructors, making it not serializable might be tricky. I need to inspect the current untracked files, as there's no BCElGamalPublicKeyTest despite dynamic aspects.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating native image resolution**\\n\\nI'm considering that resolving objects in a native image could potentially work fine. Maybe I should add `static final` fields and look into using private inner classes. The serialization method appears to need both expected properties and a verification count after closing. Then I should ensure the count during deserialization. This will help prove that the execution was successful by observing the property/group objects through internal read and write methods, without altering the metadata. Time to make some edits!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_dMvK3lmaUTINt43CK8xBSOfk|fc_0f0685683da137fd0169fbe42afe6c8192a81008f65cc1dc0e", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15on/1.48/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk15on/BCElGamalPrivateKeyTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "        byte[] serializedKey = serialize(original);\n        ElGamalPrivateKey deserialized = (ElGamalPrivateKey) deserialize(serializedKey);\n", "newText": "        byte[] serializedKey = serialize(original, p, g);\n        ElGamalPrivateKey deserialized = (ElGamalPrivateKey) deserialize(serializedKey, p, g);\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static byte[] serialize(Object value) throws Exception {\n        ByteArrayOutputStream bytes = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n        try (ObjectOutputStream output = new ObjectOutputStream(bytes)) {\n            output.writeObject(value);\n        }\n        return bytes.toByteArray();\n    }\n\n    private static Object deserialize(byte[] value) throws Exception {\n        try (ObjectInputStream input = new BouncyCastleObjectInputStream(new ByteArrayInputStream(value))) {\n            return input.readObject();\n        }\n    }\n", "newText": "    private static byte[] serialize(Object value, BigInteger p, BigInteger g) throws Exception {\n        ByteArrayOutputStream bytes = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n        try (CountingObjectOutputStream output = new CountingObjectOutputStream(bytes, p, g)) {\n            output.writeObject(value);\n            assertThat(output.getParameterObjectCount()).isEqualTo(2);\n        }\n        return bytes.toByteArray();\n    }\n\n    private static Object deserialize(byte[] value, BigInteger p, BigInteger g) throws Exception {\n        try (CountingObjectInputStream input = new CountingObjectInputStream(new ByteArrayInputStream(value), p, g)) {\n            Object deserialized = input.readObject();\n            assertThat(input.getParameterObjectCount()).isEqualTo(2);\n            return deserialized;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class CountingObjectOutputStream extends ObjectOutputStream {\n        private final BigInteger p;\n        private final BigInteger g;\n        private int parameterObjectCount;\n\n        private CountingObjectOutputStream(ByteArrayOutputStream output, BigInteger p, BigInteger g) throws Exception {\n            super(output);\n            this.p = p;\n            this.g = g;\n            enableReplaceObject(true);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Object replaceObject(Object object) throws IOException {\n            if (p.equals(object) || g.equals(object)) {\n                parameterObjectCount++;\n            }\n            return super.replaceObject(object);\n        }\n\n        private int getParameterObjectCount() {\n            return parameterObjectCount;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class CountingObjectInputStream extends BouncyCastleObjectInputStream {\n        private final BigInteger p;\n        private final BigInteger g;\n        private int parameterObjectCount;\n\n        private CountingObjectInputStream(ByteArrayInputStream input, BigInteger p, BigInteger g) throws Exception {\n            super(input);\n            this.p = p;\n            this.g = g;\n            enableResolveObject(true);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Object resolveObject(Object object) throws IOException {\n            if (p.equals(object) || g.equals(object)) {\n                parameterObjectCount++;\n            }\n            return super.resolveObject(object);\n        }\n\n        private int getParameterObjectCount() {\n            return parameterObjectCount;\n        }\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 729, "output": 2135, "cacheRead": 46592, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 49456, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778115605094, "responseId": "resp_0f0685683da137fd0169fbe415b9c881928937b2be3bdb7903"}}
